EF Explanation:

1. EmpDBEntities is your Entity Framework DbContext class.
It represents:
•	Your Database
•	All Tables inside the database as DbSet properties

2. db.Empls
Empls is a DbSet<Empl>
It represents the Employee table in the database.
So:
•	db.Empls.ToList() → SELECT * FROM Empls
•	db.Empls.Find(id) → SELECT * FROM Empls WHERE id = ?
•	db.Empls.Add(emp) → INSERT
•	db.Empls.Remove(emp) → DELETE
•	db.SaveChanges() → Executes SQL in database
